import numpy as np
import pandas as pd

# Generate random values based on the provided statistics
target_materials = ["plastic", "aluminium", "polypropylene", "polystyrene"]
thicknesses = np.random.uniform(0, 125, 25)
pulse_widths = np.random.uniform(24, 12900, 25)
energies = np.random.uniform(0.3, 1000, 25)
spot_sizes = np.random.uniform(2.13, 60, 25)
intensities = np.random.uniform(1e18, 5.59e21, 25)
powers = np.random.uniform(1.76e11, 3.83e14, 25)
cutoff_energies = np.random.uniform(3.3, 95, 25)

# Combine the generated values into a dataframe
data = pd.DataFrame({
    "target_material": np.random.choice(target_materials, 25),
    "target_thickness": thicknesses,
    "pulse_width": pulse_widths,
    "energy": energies,
    "spot_size": spot_sizes,
    "intensity": intensities,
    "power": powers,
    "cutoff_energy": cutoff_energies
})

# Print the generated data points
print(data)
```
